{"word":"H5095 - נָהַל - nâhal - naw-hal' - Carry","slug":"H5095","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָהַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâhal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-hal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Carry"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D4;&#x05DC; - na&#x0302;hal</b> - <i>naw-hal'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to run with a <i>sparkle</i>, that is, <i>flow</i>; hence (transitively) to <i>conduct</i>, and (by inference) to <i>protect</i>, <i>sustain: - </i>carry, feed, guide, lead (gently, on)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5096\">H5096</a>, <a href=\"#/H5097\">H5097</a>"}]}